        "pages": {
            "product": {
                "header": "Put your powers of persuasion to the ultimate test, on a whole new planet!",
                "about": " Mars Generation One: Argubot Academy is an argumentation adventure game for iOS tablets and coming soon to Android. Aligned to Common Core argumentation standards on Reasoning and Evidence, it lets players construct special robots called argubots and pit them against each other to resolve conflicts and make important decisions.  In its exciting first-city-on-Mars environment, the game setting presents inspirational STEM content that places the player in the fiction of a small community on the red planet.",
                "curriculum": [
                    "Addresses critical Common Core standards in persuasion and reasoned thinking – a cornerstone of the standards for English Language Arts",
                    "Promotes interest in STEM content while developing the literacy and leadership skills that are essential for any 21st century career",
                    "With input from experts in literacy at the National Writing Project, works well to introduce norms for classroom discussions, persuasive writing, and expository writing",
                    "Brings games into the ELA classroom to support Common Core Reading and Writing so that educators can make the most of their tablet hardware"
                    
